description.plain:
Moneybagg Yo (born September 22, 1991) is a platinum-selling recording artist from Memphis, Tennessee who is affiliated with Yo Gotti. He is a signee of Gotti’s Collective Music Group (CMG) in partnership with N-Less Entertainment and Interscope Records.

Following the August 2018 release of Bet On Me, Bagg found the hip-hop spotlights with release of RESET and 43VA HEARTLESS. In 2020, he released his third studio album, Time Served, and its deluxe edition.

Bagg climbed the Billboard Hot 100 in 2021, securing his first No. 1 album with A Gangsta’s Pain, supported by hit singles such as “Wockesha” and “Time Today.”

“Time Today” serves as Moneybagg Yo’s first release of 2021 and also serves as the lead single to his chart-topping fourth studio album, A Gangsta’s Pain. The song is produced by RealRed and YC.

On the song, Moneybagg Yo raps about haters and fake friends, resolving to be more cautious, while also boasting about his expensive possessions, specifically watches and jewelry. He first teased a snippet on February 1, 2021, confirming its release in the month, revealing the specific date one day later.

The official music video for the song premiered eleven hours after its release on February 3, 2021.

Important is a standout Single on MoneyBagg’s Mixtape  Federal 3X.
 He’s come a long way in this game called life. Bagg is  leveling up from being pushing yayo

to signing with Yo Gotti’s label CMG  and getting a $250 000 Cash advance for signing a 1 million dollar deal. An important Milestone in his career.

He raps of how XXL magazine snubbed Bagg from the 2017 Freshman list. Along with this Bagg makes references to the Patek Phillipe  watches that he  rocks on his wrists since his long awaited come up.

He’s important now cause he not only has overcome buzz which is associated with newcomers but that hes solidifying his name in rap and is on the road to become established and stardom.

songs.title: Say Na

description.plain:
“Say Na” is the first collaboration between Moneybagg Yo and J. Cole.

In an interview with Vulture published in April 2018, J. Cole stated that he could not get Lil Baby and Moneybagg’s track  “All of a Sudden” out of his head.

Months later, Moneybagg caught up with J. Cole on the LA stop of the KOD Tour, and he played some music for him. Moneybagg wanted to collaborate on a song that was Cole’s style, but Cole told him that he wanted to “come to [MoneyBagg’s] world.” Moneybagg posted a picture of their chance meeting on August 29, 2018, which led to rumors of an imminent collaboration.



“Say Na” is produced by DrumGod, a beatmaker from Ohio who handled production for several tracks on Bet on Me. Javar Rockamore, who worked with Moneybagg on “Mandatory Drug Test,” also co-produced the track.

Moneybagg teased the song on Instagram Live:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_WvjpB8KbGM
